parameters.name: Vol 0
parameters.description: Index number of the first of two 96-second telemetry volumes in the data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Vol 1
parameters.description: Index number of the second of two 96-second telemetry volumes in the data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Time start
parameters.description: Beginning of the 192-second data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Time stop
parameters.description: End of the 192-second data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Hour
parameters.description: Midpoint of the 192-second data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Hour start
parameters.description: Beginning of the 192-second data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Hour stop
parameters.description: End of the 192-second data accumulation interval

parameters.name: Counts
parameters.description: Number of protons counted by the LET telescope in this energy channel during the data accumulation interval

parameters.name: One-count flux
parameters.description: log10 of flux represented by one proton count during the data accumuation interval, accounting for geometry factor, accumulation time, energy channel width, and deadtime correction

parameters.name: Log flux
parameters.description: Flux measurement for the data accumulation interval - if N is the number of counts and F is the one-count flux from the previous two entries, then this measurement is F * N

parameters.name: Log flux low
parameters.description: 1-sigma lower limit to flux measurement for the data accumuation interval - if N > 0 this is F * (N - sqrt(N - 0.25))

parameters.name: Log flux high
parameters.description: 1-sigma upper limit to flux measurement for the data accumuation interval - F * (N + 1 + sqrt(N + 0.75))

parameters.name: S/C L
parameters.description: L value for particles mirroring at the spacecraft location at the midpoint of the data accumulatin interval

parameters.name: S/C L start
parameters.description: L value for particles mirroring at the spacecraft location at the beginning of the data accumulatin interval

parameters.name: S/C L stop
parameters.description: L value for particles mirroring at the spacecraft location at the end of the data accumulatin interval

parameters.name: G/C L
parameters.description: L value for guiding center of protons at the midpoint energy of this channel coming down the sensor's boresight at the midpoint of the data accumulatin interval

parameters.name: G/C L start
parameters.description: L value for guiding center of protons at the midpoint energy of this channel coming down the sensor's boresight at the beginning of the data accumulatin interval

parameters.name: G/C L stop
parameters.description: L value for guiding center of protons at the midpoint energy of this channel coming down the sensor's boresight at the end of the data accumulatin interval
